# aws_glue_catalog_table

Provides a Glue Catalog Table Resource. You can refer to the Glue Developer Guide for a full explanation of the Glue Data Catalog functionality.

## input variables

| Name | Description | Type | Default | Required |
|------|-------------|:----:|:-----:|:-----:|
|account_id|The id of AWS account.|string||Yes|
|region|This is the AWS region.|string|us-east-1|Yes|
|glue_catalog_table_name|Name of the table. For Hive compatibility, this must be entirely lowercase.|string|{{ name }}|No|
|glue_catalog_table_database_name|Name of the metadata database where the table metadata resides. For Hive compatibility, this must be all lowercase.|string|{{ name }}|No|
|glue_catalog_table_catalog_id|ID of the Glue Catalog and database to create the table in. If omitted, this defaults to the AWS Account ID plus the database name.|string|{{ name }}|No|
|glue_catalog_table_description|Description of the table.|string|Managed by TerraHub|No|
|glue_catalog_table_partition_keys_columns|A list of columns by which the table is partitioned. Only primitive types are supported as partition keys.|list|[]|No|
|glue_catalog_table_type|The type of this table (EXTERNAL_TABLE, VIRTUAL_VIEW, etc.).|string|EXTERNAL_TABLE|No|
|glue_catalog_table_parameters|Properties associated with this table, as a list of key-value pairs.|map|{classification = "json"}|No|
|glue_catalog_table_storage_descriptor_columns|A list of the Columns in the table.|list|[]|No|
|glue_catalog_table_storage_descriptor_location|The physical location of the table. By default this takes the form of the warehouse location, followed by the database location in the warehouse, followed by the table name.|string|s3:|No|
|glue_catalog_table_storage_descriptor_input_format|The input format: SequenceFileInputFormat (binary), or TextInputFormat, or a custom format.|string|org.apache.hadoop.mapred.TextInputFormat|No|
|glue_catalog_table_storage_descriptor_output_format|The output format: SequenceFileOutputFormat (binary), or IgnoreKeyTextOutputFormat, or a custom format.|string|org.apache.hadoop.hive.ql.io.HiveIgnoreKeyTextOutputFormat|No|
|glue_catalog_table_storage_descriptor_ser_de_info|Serialization/deserialization (SerDe) information.|list|[]|No|
|glue_catalog_table_storage_descriptor_sort_columns|A list of Order objects specifying the sort order of each bucket in the table.|list|[]|No|

